<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-26T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/905: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-27T10:00:00+08:00">October 27, 1930—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:15 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>933. Department’s 355, October 17, 9 p.m. I see no objection to your
                            informing Davis of my conversation with Moss. I am urging Foreign Office
                            to reply to the Legation’s note of October 31, 1929.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>